In a #small pot{}, combine @Jasmine Rice{3/4%cup}, 1 1/4 cups water
(2 cups for 4 servings), and a pinch of @salt{}. Bring to a boil, then
cover and reduce heat to low; cook until rice is tender, ~{15-18%minutes}.
Keep covered off heat until ready to serve.

Wash and dry produce. Peel and mince @Garlic{1%clove}(minced). Trim and
halve @Mini Cucumber{2} lengthwise; cut into 1⁄2-inch-thick half-moons.

Transfer cucumbers to a #medium bowl{}; cover with @salt{pinch} and toss
to coat. Let sit for ~{3-5%minutes}, then rinse and drain. Return to bowl.

Meanwhile, pat @Chopped Chicken Breast{10%ounce}(cut into bite-size pieces)
dry with #paper towels{}; cut into bite-size pieces if necessary. Season
with a pinch of @salt{} and @pepper{}.

Heat a drizzle of @cooking oil{} in a #large pan{} over medium-high heat.
Add chicken and cook, stirring occasionally, until browned, ~{2-3%minutes}.

Reduce heat to medium and add @Umami Ginger Sauce{4%tablespoon},
@Sweet Thai Chili Sauce{1%ounce}, and @Ponzu Sauce{18%milliliters};
cook, stirring occasionally, until thickened, ~{2-3%minutes}. Taste and
season with salt and pepper as needed.

To bowl with cucumbers, add @Gochujang Sauce{1/2%ounce}, garlic, half the
@Sesame Oil{1/2%tablespoon}, remaining ponzu, @Sugar{1%tsp}, and
@Korean Chili Flakes{1%teaspoon} to taste. Toss to coat.

Fluff rice with a #fork{}.

Divide rice and chicken between #bowls{} in separate sections. Top with
smashed cucumbers and @Peanuts{1/2%ounce}. Serve.

> Chicken is fully cooked when internal temperature reaches 165º.